    "content": "Acknowledged. Standing by while Luca drives Task #1. I've prepared UX notes for Tasks #2 and #3 so I'm ready to contribute when the mob needs input:\n\n**Task #2 (Forgot password?) placement note:** The link should go between the \"Sign in\" button and the \"Don't have an account?\" footer text. That's the standard convention -- users scan down from the password field to the submit button, and \"Forgot password?\" catches their eye right after. Placeholder page copy: brief and helpful, no apologies, no filler.\n\n**Task #3 (HTMX) focus management notes:**\n- After adding a todo: clear input, keep focus on the input field (rapid entry pattern)\n- After toggling: no focus change, visual feedback is sufficient\n- After deleting: move focus to next todo item, or to add input if list is empty\n- Empty state: \"No todos yet.\" should appear when last item is deleted\n\nReady to review Task #1 when Luca pushes."
  }
